In [8]:
title=[]
start_year=[]
end_year=[]
rating=[]
genre=[]
runtime=[]
casting=[]
votes=[]
certificate=[]

#using for loop to extract the data through range.
for i in range(1,11):
    print("""https://www.imdb.com/search/keyword/?keywords=web-series&sort=moviemeter,asc&mode=detail&page="""+str(i)+"""&ref_=kw_nxt""")
    url = """https://www.imdb.com/search/keyword/?keywords=web-series&sort=moviemeter,asc&mode=detail&page="""+str(i)+"""&ref_=kw_nxt"""
    page = requests.get(url)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.text)
#titles

    titles=soup.find_all("h3",class_="lister-item-header")

    for i in titles:
        a=i.text
        t_=a.split('\n')[2]
        if t_:
            title.append(t_)
        else:
            title.append(np.nan)

#start year

    d=soup.find_all('span',class_="lister-item-year text-muted unbold")

    for i in d:
        b=i.text
        c=re.findall(r'\W(\d+)\W',b)
        if (len(c))>0:
            start_year.append(c)
        else:
            start_year.append(np.nan)

#end year

    container=soup.find_all('div',class_='lister-item mode-detail')
    for i in container:
        d = re.findall('\–(\d+)\)', i.text)
        if len(d)>0:
            
            end_year.append(d)
        else:
            end_year.append('2023')

#rating

    container=soup.find_all('div',class_='lister-item mode-detail')
    for i in container:
        if len(i.find_all('div',class_="inline-block ratings-imdb-rating"))>0:
            rating.append(i.find_all('div',class_="inline-block ratings-imdb-rating")[0].text)
        else:
            rating.append(np.nan) 
#genre

    container=soup.find_all('div',class_='lister-item mode-detail')
    for i in container:
        if len(i.find_all('span',class_='genre'))>0:
            genre.append(i.find_all('span',class_='genre')[0].text)
        else:
            genre.append(np.nan)
#casting  

    k=soup.find_all("div",class_="lister-item mode-detail")
    for i in k:
        b=i.text
        l=re.findall(r'Stars\:\s(.*\s.*\s.*\s.*)',b)
        if (len(l))>0:
            casting.append(l)
        else:
            casting.append(np.nan)
        

    #votes

    j=soup.find_all("div",class_="lister-item mode-detail")
    for i in j:
        b=i.text
        m=re.findall(r'Votes\:\s(\d+\,?\d+)',b)
        if (len(m))>0:
            votes.append(m)
        else:
            votes.append(np.nan)
    
    #runtime
    container=soup.find_all('div',class_='lister-item mode-detail')
    for i in container:
        if len(i.find_all('span',class_='runtime'))>0:
            runtime.append(i.find_all('span',class_='runtime')[0].text)
        else:
            runtime.append(np.nan)

#This code scrappes the data from the Url/Website within the given range i.e we have given a range (1,500,50)

def rating(rating):
    if rating>=8.5:
        return 'Excellent'
    elif rating>=7.9:
        return 'Good'
    else:
        return 'Average'
    
df['rating_cat']=df['Rating'].apply(rating)
